# Packages the ``ramboot-init`` variant needs that the base + flash
# lists don't pull in. live-build consumes every ``*.list.chroot``
# unconditionally so these get installed in the netboot-pc + usbboot-pc
# chroots too -- harmless extra ~3 MB and the tools have no
# auto-start surface; the alternative (variant-conditional package
# lists) is not honoured reliably in our build environment's
# live-build (see the comment in ``pixie-base.list.chroot`` on the
# ``.list.chroot_<arch>`` story).
#
# What each is used for in the ramboot path:
#
#   * ``nbd-client`` -- the in-initrd binary the ``/init`` script
#     invokes to expose nbdmux's named export as ``/dev/nbd0``.
#   * ``busybox-static`` -- shell + utilities the initramfs needs
#     before any libc is pivoted in. Static so it doesn't depend
#     on the chroot's libc layout.
nbd-client
busybox-static
